  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, I can confirm that **money laundering** is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering is the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This makes the money appear to come from a legitimate source.\n\n### Why is it illegal?\nMoney laundering is considered a serious crime because:\n1. It enables criminal activities (e.g., drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, terrorism) to continue and profit.\n2. It undermines the integrity of financial systems.\n3. It can destabilize economies and harm society.\n\n### Legal Consequences:\nPenalties for money laundering vary by jurisdiction but often include:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Seizure of assets\n- Blacklisting from financial systems\n\nIf you have further questions or need clarification, feel free to ask!",
